Romantsev back in the hot seat at Spartak
Georgy Yartsev, head coach of Russian champions Spartak Moscow, has
been replaced by club president and former national team coach Oleg
Romantsev, it was announced here on Monday.
ITAR-TASS reported that Romantsev, previously in charge for a six-year
spell, will resume coaching duties with the team.
Yartsev, 48, guided Spartak to the league title last month in his first
season. He will be retained as Romantsev's assistant.
